{
  "stem": "22586.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the last thing I remember about my father was he came over to us and said-- apparently he-- he must have known where we were, because he said to us, to my sister and me, wherever you go, they ask you if you know how to do anything, always say yes.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And I think it stood me in good-- that was very good advice he gave me, because it helped me later on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's the last time I saw him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You're now at Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] You were able to stay with your sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What was your life like?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What was-- what did you do there?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were put into a barrack that had [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] wooden-- what do you call those?-- where we slept-- wooden [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] like bunks.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you have a lot of women sleeping together in these bunks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the morning, we would get a piece of bread and coffee.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then in the afternoon, we would get a soup.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very early in the morning-- oh.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How could I forget?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we first came to Auschwitz, we were taken to a-- an area where-- we were marched to an area where they shaved our heads.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We're undressed and given gray dresses, no underwear, just a gray dress and wooden shoes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then we were taken back to these barracks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the way to the place where they shaved our heads and took our clothing, there was a big ditch, where apparently people from the train who couldn't-- who were too sick to move were put into these ditches with the dead, the living with the dead, just left there.",
      "word_count": 50
    }
  ],
